attachments.title: How One Guy in Oregon Made the Best U.S. Map You’ll Ever See
attachments.text: American mapmaking’s most prestigious honor is the “Best of Show” award at the annual competition of the Cartography and Geographic Information Society. The five most recent winners were all maps designed by large, well-known institutions: National Geographic (three times), the Central Intelligence Agency Cartography Center, and the U.S. Census Bureau....
attachments.fallback: Slate Magazine: How One Guy in Oregon Made the Best U.S. Map You’ll Ever See

text: This is cool. Reminds me of the process used for maps in various fictional worlds in games. Similar attention to detail, usually different scale.
